---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Header.astro";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="International Women's Day | The Latina Sweat Project"
  description="Honoring International Women's Day (8M) - The Latina Sweat Project stands in solidarity with women across the globe, especially in Mexico, where women march for justice against feminicide."
>
  <Header />
  <main>
    {/* Hero */}
    <section class="relative bg-purple-950 py-16 sm:py-24 overflow-hidden">
      <div
        class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-900/80 via-purple-950 to-purple-900/60"
      >
      </div>
      <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div
          class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 items-center gap-10 lg:gap-16"
        >
          <div class="text-center lg:text-left">
            <p
              class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-purple-300"
            >
              March 8th
            </p>
            <h1
              class="mt-4 font-sans text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl"
            >
              Honoring<br />
              <span class="text-purple-300">International Women's Day</span>
            </h1>
            <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-purple-200/80 font-medium">
              Dia Internacional de la Mujer &middot; 8 de Marzo
            </p>
            <p
              class="mt-6 max-w-2xl font-body text-lg text-purple-100/70 sm:text-xl leading-relaxed mx-auto lg:mx-0"
            >
              As a studio founded and built by Mexican women, we honor this day
              by standing in solidarity with women across the globe, especially
              in Mexico, where women march for their rights and for justice.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-md lg:max-w-none">
            <img
              src={`${base}images/iwd-banner.png`}
              alt="International Women's Day - Juntas Somos Mas Fuertes - Dia Internacional de la Mujer, 8 de Marzo"
              class="w-full rounded-2xl shadow-2xl shadow-purple-900/50"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Wear Purple Banner */}
    <section class="bg-purple-600 py-4">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <p class="text-white font-bold text-base sm:text-lg">
          Wear purple on March 8th to commemorate International Women's Day
          <span class="hidden sm:inline">&mdash;</span>
          <span class="block sm:inline text-purple-100 font-medium">
            Viste de morado el 8 de marzo para conmemorar el Dia Internacional
            de la Mujer
          </span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Our Statement */}
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <div
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-purple-100 border border-purple-200 px-4 py-2 mb-6"
          >
            <span
              class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-purple-700"
              >Our Statement</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="space-y-6 font-body text-lg text-medium-gray leading-relaxed"
        >
          <p>
            As a studio founded and built by Mexican women, we want to
            acknowledge today as International Women's Day. More specifically,
            we want to bring attention to what this day means on a global level,
            and in particular in Mexico, where women across the country march
            for their rights and for justice in a country where feminicide is
            all too prevalent.
          </p>
          <p>
            As they move their bodies in marches and in resistance, we move ours
            in solidarity with them from afar.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 border-l-4 border-purple-400 pl-6">
          <div
            class="space-y-6 font-body text-lg text-medium-gray leading-relaxed italic"
          >
            <p>
              Como un estudio fundado y construido por mujeres mexicanas,
              queremos conmemorar hoy el Dia Internacional de la Mujer. Mas
              especificamente, queremos llamar la atencion al significado de
              este dia a nivel global, y en particular en Mexico, donde mujeres
              en todo el pais marchan por sus derechos y por justicia en un pais
              donde el feminicidio es demasiado prevalente.
            </p>
            <p>
              Mientras ellas mueven sus cuerpos en las marchas y en resistencia,
              nosotras movemos los nuestros en solidaridad con ellas desde la
              distancia.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Femicide vs Feminicide */}
    <section class="bg-purple-50 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="text-center mb-10">
          <h2
            class="font-sans text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-off-black sm:text-4xl"
          >
            Femicide vs Feminicide
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-1 text-lg text-purple-600 font-medium">
            Femicidio vs Feminicidio
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="rounded-2xl bg-white p-8 sm:p-10 shadow-sm border border-purple-100"
        >
          <div
            class="space-y-6 font-body text-lg text-medium-gray leading-relaxed"
          >
            <p>
              In English, <strong class="text-off-black">femicide</strong> is the
              word most commonly used to describe the murder of women by men. <strong
                class="text-off-black">Feminicide</strong
              > has become a term to describe femicide in the context of the systemic
              failure to protect women and the impunity that is often seen in these
              cases.
            </p>
            <p>
              This word has become widely used across Latin America to better
              describe the complexity and specificity of the issue &mdash; it
              names not just the act of violence, but the structural conditions
              that allow it to continue.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-8 border-l-4 border-purple-400 pl-6">
            <div
              class="space-y-6 font-body text-lg text-medium-gray leading-relaxed italic"
            >
              <p>
                En ingles, <strong class="text-off-black not-italic"
                  >femicidio</strong
                > es la palabra mas comun para describir el asesinato de mujeres por
                hombres. <strong class="text-off-black not-italic"
                  >Feminicidio</strong
                > se ha vuelto una palabra para describir el femicidio en el contexto
                del problema sistematico y el fracaso de proteger a las mujeres y
                la impunidad que se ve a menudo en estos casos.
              </p>
              <p>
                Esta palabra se ha vuelto ampliamente utilizada en Latinoamerica
                para describir mejor la complejidad y especificidad del asunto.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Key stats */}
        <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div
            class="rounded-xl bg-white p-6 border border-purple-100 text-center"
          >
            <p class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-purple-700">8M</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-medium-gray font-medium">
              March 8th has become a symbol of feminist resistance across Latin
              America, with massive marches in cities throughout Mexico and the
              region.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            class="rounded-xl bg-white p-6 border border-purple-100 text-center"
          >
            <p class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-purple-700">Ni Una Mas</p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-medium-gray font-medium">
              "Not one more" &mdash; a rallying cry demanding an end to violence
              against women and accountability from governments and
              institutions.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* Resources */}
    <section class="py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="text-center mb-14">
          <div
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-purple-100 border border-purple-200 px-4 py-2 mb-6"
          >
            <span
              class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-purple-700"
              >Learn More</span
            >
          </div>
          <h2
            class="font-sans text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-off-black sm:text-4xl"
          >
            Resources &amp; References
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-1 text-lg text-purple-600 font-medium">
            Recursos y Referencias
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 mx-auto max-w-2xl font-body text-lg text-medium-gray">
            If you're interested in learning more about 8M and feminicide in
            Mexico, here are some resources we recommend.
          </p>
        </div>

        {/* Music */}
        <div class="mb-12">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
            <div
              class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-purple-100"
            >
              <svg
                class="h-5 w-5 text-purple-700"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
              >
                <path
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  d="M9 19V6l12-3v13M9 19c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zm12-3c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zM9 10l12-3"
                ></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-sans text-xl font-bold text-off-black">
              Music / Musica
            </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <a
              href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oeU7rb-dBow"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="group rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5 transition-all hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md hover:border-purple-300"
            >
              <p
                class="font-bold text-off-black group-hover:text-purple-700 transition-colors"
              >
                Si Me Matan
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-1">Silvana Estrada</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-purple-500 mt-2 font-medium">
                Watch on YouTube &rarr;
              </p>
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VLLyzqkH6cs"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="group rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5 transition-all hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md hover:border-purple-300"
            >
              <p
                class="font-bold text-off-black group-hover:text-purple-700 transition-colors"
              >
                Cancion sin miedo
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-1">
                Vivir Quintana ft. Palomar
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-purple-500 mt-2 font-medium">
                Watch on YouTube &rarr;
              </p>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Podcast */}
        <div class="mb-12">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
            <div
              class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-purple-100"
            >
              <svg
                class="h-5 w-5 text-purple-700"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
              >
                <path
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  d="M19 11a7 7 0 01-7 7m0 0a7 7 0 01-7-7m7 7v4m0 0H8m4 0h4m-4-8a3 3 0 01-3-3V5a3 3 0 116 0v6a3 3 0 01-3 3z"
                ></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-sans text-xl font-bold text-off-black">Podcast</h3>
          </div>
          <a
            href="https://www.diezmujeres.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="group rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5 transition-all hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md hover:border-purple-300 block max-w-md"
          >
            <p
              class="font-bold text-off-black group-hover:text-purple-700 transition-colors"
            >
              10 Mujeres
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-1">
              A podcast exploring the stories and struggles of women in Mexico.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xs text-purple-500 mt-2 font-medium">
              Listen now &rarr;
            </p>
          </a>
        </div>

        {/* Books */}
        <div class="mb-12">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
            <div
              class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-purple-100"
            >
              <svg
                class="h-5 w-5 text-purple-700"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
              >
                <path
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253"
                ></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-sans text-xl font-bold text-off-black">
              Books / Libros
            </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5">
              <p class="font-bold text-off-black">
                El invencible verano de Liliana
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-0.5 italic">
                Liliana's Invincible Summer
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-purple-600 mt-2 font-medium">
                Cristina Rivera Garza
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-medium-gray mt-2">
                Winner of the 2024 Pulitzer Prize, this memoir traces the life
                and murder of the author's sister, confronting Mexico's epidemic
                of gender violence with unflinching tenderness.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5">
              <p class="font-bold text-off-black">Not One More!</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-0.5 italic">
                Feminicidio on the Border
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-purple-600 mt-2 font-medium">
                Nina Maria Lozano
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-medium-gray mt-2">
                Examines the activist mothers and families seeking justice for
                victims of feminicide along the US-Mexico border.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5">
              <p class="font-bold text-off-black">The Femicide Machine</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-purple-600 mt-2 font-medium">
                Sergio Gonzalez Rodriguez
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-medium-gray mt-2">
                A foundational investigation into the murders of women in Ciudad
                Juarez, exposing the systemic machinery of violence and
                impunity.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5">
              <p class="font-bold text-off-black">More or Less Dead</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-0.5 italic">
                Feminicide, Haunting, and the Ethics of Representation in Mexico
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-purple-600 mt-2 font-medium">
                Alice Driver
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-medium-gray mt-2">
                A critical examination of how feminicide is represented in
                media, art, and activism, questioning the ethics of bearing
                witness.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div
              class="rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5 sm:col-span-2"
            >
              <p class="font-bold text-off-black">Counting Feminicide</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-0.5 italic">
                Data Feminism in Action
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-purple-600 mt-2 font-medium">
                Catherine D'Ignazio
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-medium-gray mt-2">
                Explores how activists and data scientists are using data to
                make feminicide visible and hold governments accountable for the
                crisis.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Videos & Film */}
        <div class="mb-12">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
            <div
              class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-purple-100"
            >
              <svg
                class="h-5 w-5 text-purple-700"
                fill="currentColor"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              >
                <path d="M8 5v14l11-7z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-sans text-xl font-bold text-off-black">
              Videos &amp; Film
            </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <a
              href="https://www.netflix.com/title/81002192"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="group rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5 transition-all hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md hover:border-purple-300"
            >
              <p
                class="font-bold text-off-black group-hover:text-purple-700 transition-colors"
              >
                The Three Deaths of Marisela Escobedo
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-1">
                A documentary following the relentless fight of a mother seeking
                justice for her daughter's feminicide in Chihuahua, Mexico. Her
                story became a symbol of the failures of the justice system.
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-purple-500 mt-2 font-medium">
                Watch on Netflix &rarr;
              </p>
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://www.netflix.com/title/81498010"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="group rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5 transition-all hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md hover:border-purple-300"
            >
              <p
                class="font-bold text-off-black group-hover:text-purple-700 transition-colors"
              >
                Ruido (Noise)
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-1">
                A film about a mother searching for her missing daughter in
                Mexico City, shedding light on the epidemic of missing women and
                the collective grief of searching families.
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-purple-500 mt-2 font-medium">
                Watch on Netflix &rarr;
              </p>
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_4XILJP7OyQ"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="group rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5 transition-all hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md hover:border-purple-300 sm:col-span-2"
            >
              <p
                class="font-bold text-off-black group-hover:text-purple-700 transition-colors"
              >
                AbiertaMENTE: Frida &mdash; Una guerra contra el feminicidio
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-1">
                An in-depth look at the fight against feminicide through the
                lens of those on the front lines of the movement in Mexico.
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-purple-500 mt-2 font-medium">
                Watch on YouTube &rarr;
              </p>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* Articles & Research */}
        <div class="mb-12">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
            <div
              class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-purple-100"
            >
              <svg
                class="h-5 w-5 text-purple-700"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
              >
                <path
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  d="M19 20H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h10a2 2 0 012 2v1m2 13a2 2 0 01-2-2V7m2 13a2 2 0 002-2V9a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2m-4-3H9M7 16h6M7 8h6v4H7V8z"
                ></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-sans text-xl font-bold text-off-black">
              Articles / Articulos
            </h3>
          </div>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <a
              href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/28259597_Del_femicidio_al_feminicidio"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="group rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5 block transition-all hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md hover:border-purple-300"
            >
              <p
                class="font-bold text-off-black group-hover:text-purple-700 transition-colors"
              >
                Del femicidio al feminicidio
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-1">
                By Marcela Lagarde de los Rios &mdash; a foundational academic
                text that traces the evolution from the concept of femicide to
                feminicide, establishing the framework used across Latin
                American legal and activist movements.
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-purple-500 mt-2 font-medium">
                Read on ResearchGate &rarr;
              </p>
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://www.unwomen.org/en/articles/explainer/five-essential-facts-to-know-about-femicide"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="group rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5 block transition-all hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md hover:border-purple-300"
            >
              <p
                class="font-bold text-off-black group-hover:text-purple-700 transition-colors"
              >
                5 Essential Facts to Know About Femicide
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-1">
                UN Women provides critical global data and context on
                gender-based killings of women and girls worldwide.
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-purple-500 mt-2 font-medium">
                Read on UN Women &rarr;
              </p>
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://malvestida.com/2022/03/marcha-8m-ciudad-de-mexico/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="group rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5 block transition-all hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md hover:border-purple-300"
            >
              <p
                class="font-bold text-off-black group-hover:text-purple-700 transition-colors"
              >
                Asi fue la marcha del #8M en Ciudad de Mexico
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-1">
                "No tenemos miedo, tenemos fuego" &mdash; a firsthand account of
                the massive women's march in Mexico City.
              </p>
              <p class="text-xs text-purple-500 mt-2 font-medium">
                Read on Malvestida &rarr;
              </p>
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://malvestida.com/2023/03/ilustraciones-del-8-de-marzo-para-compartir/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="group rounded-xl bg-purple-50 border border-purple-100 p-5 block transition-all hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-md hover:border-purple-300"
            >
              <p
                class="font-bold text-off-black group-hover:text-purple-700 transition-colors"
              >
                Ilustraciones del 8 de marzo para compartir
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-medium-gray mt-1">
                A collection of powerful illustrations created for International
                Women's Day, visualizing the movement and its messages.
              </p>
